President Muhammadu Buhari on Monday night received National Leader of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Asiwaju Bola Tinubu, and pioneer Interim Chairman of the party, Chief Bisi Akande, at the Presidential Villa, Abuja. The visit, which held at the President’s official residence, was to pay condolences to Buhari over last Friday’s air crash, which claimed Chief of Army Staff, Lt. Gen. Ibrahim Attahiru, and ten other officers and men in Kaduna. Asiwaju Tinubu and Chief Akande were accompanied by some other members of the party on the visit.